node.text:
The most charming houses from @learncraftgrow!

Reposted from @learncraftgrow One of our all time favourites! 🙂🌈⁣
⁣⁣
🏙 PAPER ROLL BUILDINGS 🏙⁣⁣⁣
Instead of throwing away your paper rolls, collect them to make a little city with these cool and colourful buildings! ⁣⁣⁣
⁣
⁣⁣⁣
MATERIALS:⁣⁣⁣
⭐️ Paper rolls⁣⁣⁣
⭐️ Tempera paint⁣⁣⁣
⭐️ Paintbrush⁣⁣⁣
⭐️ Coloured construction paper⁣⁣⁣
⭐️ Black marker⁣⁣⁣
⭐️ Tape⁣⁣⁣
⭐️ Scissors ⁣⁣⁣
⭐️ Glue⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
INSTRUCTIONS:⁣⁣⁣
1️⃣ Paint your paper rolls different colours. Let them dry before proceeding to the next step. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
2️⃣ To form a cone for the roof: ⁣⁣⁣
✂️Cut a construction paper into a circle. ⁣✂️Cut a triangle wedge out of the circle. Bring the cut sides together and tape.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
TIP: To make sure your circle is perfectly round, trace an object such as a lid or container.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
3️⃣ Add designs to your cone roofs using your marker and stick them to the top of the paper rolls using tape.⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
4️⃣ Draw windows and doors on the coloured construction paper with your marker and cut them out. ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
5️⃣ Glue windows and doors onto the paper rolls.⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣
.⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
Amazing butterflies made from leaves by @thomasalm3ida!

Reposted from @thomasalm3ida Lepidoptera 🦋
Thomas wants to share some things he learned about butterflies:
- Butterflies are insects.
- A butterfly’s lifecycle is made up of four parts, egg, larva (caterpillars), pupa (chrysalis), and adult.
- Butterflies attach their eggs to leaves with a special glue.
- One of the largest butterflies is the Giant Swallowtail Butterfly.
- Most caterpillars are plant eaters (herbivores).
- Fully grown caterpillars attach themselves to a suitable twig or leaf before shedding their outside layer of skin to reveal a hard skin underneath known as a chrysalis.
- An adult butterfly will eventually emerge from the chrysalis where it will wait a few hours for its wings to fill with blood and dry, before flying for the first time.
- Butterflies can live in the adult stage from anywhere between a week and a year, depending on the species.
- Butterflies have four wings.
- Unfortunately, some species of butterflies are endangered, and some have already become extinct.
- Butterflies have the ability to see the colors green, red and yellow. This is useful for them when finding flowers.
- Butterflies often have brightly coloured wings with unique patterns made up of tiny scales.
- Most butterflies feed on nectar from flowers.
- Butterflies have taste receptors on their feet.
- Estimate that there are between 15000 and 20000 different species of butterfly.
- Bird-wing butterflies have large, angular wings and fly in a similar way to birds.
- Monarch butterflies are known for their long migration.

node.text:
Adorable mask from @_simply_bea_!!

Reposted from @_simply_bea_ 🐯 Roar! Today is International Tiger Day so I thought it would be fun for the kids and I to craft a cardboard Tiger. 😉

I started with cutting out the pieces for our cardboard Tiger face, I wanted a layered effect so the kids can paint the pieces individually using a sponge roller and washable paints. They also helped in gluing the pieces together and I fished up with the finer details! ☺️

Whilst our project was drying, we watched 2 documentaries on YouTube, one in German to for some extra language learning. 😁

Did you know that Tigers are the largest in the Big Cat family and they actually like water unlike most cats? 😉

Our Tiger is joining in on a few play prompts this week:

node.text:
Such a great forest from @minimadthings!!

Reposted from @minimadthings Cardboard forest...
I made this cute cardboard forest for a guest blog post for the fab @theartfulparent a little while back. Head to their website to find out more.

This week for #makecreateplay our guest host @acorns.and.aprons asked us to get crafty with TREES. To play along TAG your TREE theme crafts with #MAKECREATEPLAY and FOLLOW hosts @littlegingerstudio @minimadthings and this weeks guest host @acorns.and.aprons  I will be sharing your creations in my stories all week and Angela will pick their faves on Sunday. Each Monday we will announce a new theme and share the winners from the previous week. Don’t forget to TAG all the hosts in your posts too, that way we won’t miss your cool creations!

The concept behind #MAKECREATEPLAY is that you and your little ones create activities or crafts that they can then play with. 
In a world of over-consumption we would like to encourage people to use recycling, found natural objects, simple household materials and craft supplies in creative ways to create play.
